# SnoreMD Web - Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
#
# =============================================================================
# QUICK START (Using Deployed API)
# =============================================================================
# To connect to the already-deployed SnoreMD API, simply use:
#
#   VITE_API_URL=https://gksonzdd9g.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev
#
# This is the recommended approach for testing/evaluation.
#
# =============================================================================
# API Configuration
# =============================================================================
# The VITE_API_URL tells the frontend where to send API requests.
#
# Option 1: Use deployed AWS API (recommended for testing)
#   - No local backend setup required
#   - Test users already configured (dr-smith, dr-wilson, dr-chen)
#
# Option 2: Use local SAM API (for development)
#   - Requires Docker + SAM CLI running locally
#   - Use: VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# Option 3: Leave empty for Vite proxy (advanced)
#   - Requests go to /api and get proxied via vite.config.ts
#   - Configure VITE_API_TARGET in vite.config.ts
#
# =============================================================================

# DEPLOYED API (copy this line to your .env file):
VITE_API_URL=https://gksonzdd9g.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev

# LOCAL API (use this if running SAM locally):
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# How to Get Your Own API URL (if you deployed your own stack)
# =============================================================================
# After running `sam deploy` in the /infra directory, get your API URL:
#
# Method 1: CloudFormation Outputs
#   aws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name snoremd-app \
#     --query "Stacks[0].Outputs[?OutputKey=='ApiEndpoint'].OutputValue" \
#     --output text
#
# Method 2: API Gateway Console
#   AWS Console > API Gateway > snoremd-app > Stages > dev > Invoke URL
#
# Method 3: SAM CLI Output
#   Look for "ApiEndpoint" in the sam deploy output
#
# The URL format is:
#   https://<API_ID>.execute-api.<REGION>.amazonaws.com/<STAGE>
#
# Example:
#   https://abc123xyz.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dev
# =============================================================================
